Reasoning: The paper deals with compressed sensing and sparse approximation algorithms, which are topics covered in several arXiv CS sub-categories. cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category as it specifically deals with the design and analysis of algorithms for recovering sparse solutions of underdetermined linear systems of equations. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is also likely as the paper discusses the computational tractability of the algorithms. cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) are possible categories as the paper discusses the performance of different algorithms and their comparison. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also a possible category as the paper deals with the design and analysis of algorithms.
